!!!strict

%html
  %head
    %title Stepdown - A Cucumber analysis tool
    %link{:type => 'text/css', :rel => 'stylesheet', :href => 'styles/style.css'}

  %body
    #container
      #header
        %h1 Stepdown
      #navigation
        %ul
          %li
            %a{:href => 'http://github.com/seancaffery/step-down'}Source
          %li
            %a{:href => 'https://rubygems.org/gems/stepdown'}Ruby gem

      #content
        %h2 Overview
        %p
          The aim of Stepdown is to provide visability to highly used steps within you Cucumber feature files.
        %h3 Statistics available
        %ul
          %li Total number of scenarios
          %li Total number of steps
          %li Number of empty scenarios (scenarios without any steps) 
          %li Number of steps per scenario
          %li Number of unique steps per scenario
          %li 
            Per step
            %ul
              %li Total usage
              %li Number of scenarios
              %li Usage per scenario
              %li Scenario grouping (number of times used with another step)

        %h2 Installation
        %p
          Stepdown is available as a Ruby gem
          .code
            gem install stepdown
        %p
          Or, add the following to your Gemfile
          .code
            gem 'stepdown'
        %h2 Usage
        %p
          From the root folder of your project. This assumes step definitions are in PROJECT_ROOT/features/step_definitions and feature files are in PROJECT_ROOT/features
          .code
            stepdown
        %p
          Or, set the the directory parameters manually 
          .code
            stepdown --steps &lt;step definition directory&gt; --features &lt;feature file directory&gt;
            %br
            e.g. stepdown --steps features/step_definitions --features features


        %h2 Sample output
        %p
          Overview
        %p
          %img{:src => 'images/overview.png'}
        %p
          Step usages
        %p
          %img{:src => 'images/usages.png'}
